gungen des heutigen Alterns.  aWith which concepts can societies confront the gradual aging of their populations? In this book, various disciplines offer proposals for a different way of dealing with age and aging, and for overcoming stereotypes: the essays reflect on literary images of aging and conceptions of aging, sketch out a culture of aging based on ethics, discuss the restructuring of society into an age-free participatory society, consider possibilities for ongoing, needs-based development of expert knowledge in companies through systematic human resources development and testing for weak spots in order to alter the current conditions of aging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAgingxSocial aspects. 0aGerontology. 4aAlter. 4aAlterskultur. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDemografischer Wandel. 4aGesellschaft. 4aJapan. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKultursoziologie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLiteratur. 4aÜberalterung der Gesellschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh  aAgeing Society.  aAging Studies.  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aDemographic Change.  aJapan.  aLiterature.  aSociety.  aSociology of Culture.1 aBeck, Anja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerwig, Henriette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerz, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHülsen-Esch, Andrea von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHülsen-Esch, Andrea von, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMae, Michiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaierhofer, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://